abstract: The U.S. Senate is holding an impeachment trial on charges by the House of Representatives that President Donald Trump abused his powers and obstructed a congressional inquiry into whether he put pressure on Ukraine to investigate Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden.

lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The U.S. Senate is holding an impeachment trial on charges by the House of Representatives that President Donald Trump abused his powers and obstructed a congressional inquiry into whether he put pressure on Ukraine to investigate Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden.
headline_main: Republican Senators to Watch in Battle Over Trump Impeachment Trial Witnesses
headline_print_headline: Republican Senators to Watch in Battle Over Trump Impeachment Trial Witnesses

abstract: For a time after revelations from John Bolton’s manuscript, it looked as if the trajectory of the trial might shift.
snippet: For a time after revelations from John Bolton’s manuscript, it looked as if the trajectory of the trial might shift.
lead_paragraph: The impeachment trial was upended this week by revelations from John R. Bolton, the president’s former national security adviser, that contradict much of President Trump’s defense about freezing aid to Ukraine. The new information, laid out in a manuscript of Mr. Bolton’s coming book, left Republican senators scrambling to assess what else Mr. Bolton might disclose.

abstract: A blunter Buttigieg, a waning trial, a dig at an ice cream shop: This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: A blunter Buttigieg, a waning trial, a dig at an ice cream shop: This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: It wasn’t quite Phil Hartman-as-Bill Clinton stopping into McDonald’s for a mid-jog bite, but Biden’s unannounced stop for ice cream at a Dairy Queen in Pella, Iowa, on Thursday turned the line for fast food into a news conference. Care to know more? You’re in luck …

abstract: U.S. Republican Senator Lisa Murkowski suggested she may break with her party and vote in favour of calling additional witnesses, including former national security adviser John Bolton, in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
snippet: U.S. Republican Senator Lisa Murkowski suggested she may break with her party and vote in favour of calling additional witnesses, including former national security adviser John Bolton, in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Republican Senator Lisa Murkowski suggested she may break with her party and vote in favour of calling additional witnesses, including former national security adviser John Bolton, in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Republican U.S. Senator Suggests She May Vote for More Impeachment Witnesses
headline_print_headline: Republican U.S. Senator Suggests She May Vote for More Impeachment Witnesses

abstract: Days after Donald Trump entered the White House in 2017, Mexico's Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador stood on U.S. soil and likened the American's treatment of migrants to Nazi Germany's persecution of Jews.
snippet: Days after Donald Trump entered the White House in 2017, Mexico's Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador stood on U.S. soil and likened the American's treatment of migrants to Nazi Germany's persecution of Jews.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Days after Donald Trump entered the White House in 2017, Mexico's Andres Manuel Lopez Obrador stood on U.S. soil and likened the American's treatment of migrants to Nazi Germany's persecution of Jews.
headline_main: Mexican Leader Plays 'Matador' to Manage Trump Migration Charge
headline_print_headline: Mexican Leader Plays 'Matador' to Manage Trump Migration Charge

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives passed two pieces of legislation on Thursday seeking to rein in President Donald Trump's ability to deploy U.S. forces to fight abroad, as some lawmakers fume over his failure to fully inform them about his strategy toward Iran.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives passed two pieces of legislation on Thursday seeking to rein in President Donald Trump's ability to deploy U.S. forces to fight abroad, as some lawmakers fume over his failure to fully inform them about his strate...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives passed two pieces of legislation on Thursday seeking to rein in President Donald Trump's ability to deploy U.S. forces to fight abroad, as some lawmakers fume over his failure to fully inform them about his strategy toward Iran.
headline_main: U.S. House Passes Measures Seeking to Pull War Powers Back From Trump
headline_print_headline: U.S. House Passes Measures Seeking to Pull War Powers Back From Trump

abstract: The Trump administration on Thursday said it will allow Russian, Chinese and European companies to continue their work at Iranian nuclear sites, arguing that their presence makes it harder for Tehran to develop nuclear weapons.
snippet: The Trump administration on Thursday said it will allow Russian, Chinese and European companies to continue their work at Iranian nuclear sites, arguing that their presence makes it harder for Tehran to develop nuclear weapons.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON/PARIS — The Trump administration on Thursday said it will allow Russian, Chinese and European companies to continue their work at Iranian nuclear sites, arguing that their presence makes it harder for Tehran to develop nuclear weapons.
headline_main: U.S. Renews Waivers on Iran Nuclear Work, but Sanctions Top Iran Nuclear Official
headline_print_headline: U.S. Renews Waivers on Iran Nuclear Work, but Sanctions Top Iran Nuclear Official

abstract: Palestinians around the world are uniting to thwart U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan, former Hamas leader Khaled Meshaal said, criticising Arab governments who supported the plan.
snippet: Palestinians around the world are uniting to thwart U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan, former Hamas leader Khaled Meshaal said, criticising Arab governments who supported the plan.
lead_paragraph: DOHA — Palestinians around the world are uniting to thwart U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan, former Hamas leader Khaled Meshaal said, criticising Arab governments who supported the plan.
headline_main: Hamas' Meshaal Says Palestinians Working to Foil Trump Plan
headline_print_headline: Hamas' Meshaal Says Palestinians Working to Foil Trump Plan

abstract: Amy McGrath, a former Marine combat aviator who has raised more than $16 million in her effort to challenge Sen. Mitch McConnell in November’s election, said Friday that she was endorsing Joe Biden for president.
snippet: Amy McGrath, a former Marine combat aviator who has raised more than $16 million in her effort to challenge Sen. Mitch McConnell in November’s election, said Friday that she was endorsing Joe Biden for president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Amy McGrath, a former Marine combat aviator who has raised more than $16 million in her effort to challenge Sen. Mitch McConnell in November’s election, said Friday that she was endorsing Joe Biden for president.
headline_main: McConnell's Democratic Rival McGrath Endorses Biden for 2020
headline_print_headline: McConnell's Democratic Rival McGrath Endorses Biden for 2020
